 Out of 774 local government areas in Nigeria, only 13 of them in just four states have attained Open Defecation Free status August 2, 2019 In "Viewpoint" The Deputy Director, Niger Ministry of Health, Hajiya Rakiya Datti, has said that over 80 per cent of diseases such as cholera, diarrhoea, polio and Ebola are contacted through open defecation. November 26, 2014 In "News" The Katsina State Rural Water Supply and Sanitation Agency (RUWASSA) says it is collaborating with traditional institutions to stop open defecation in the state. June 17, 2018 In "Health"